        <updateDate>2025-07-29T18:41:08Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bus Rolling Stock Modernization Act of 2024&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill allows a state or local authority (e.g., a transit authority) to use public transportation grants to make a partial advance payment for bus rolling stock (e.g., transit buses).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, a public transportation grant recipient may use grant funds to make an advance payment of not more than 20% of the total purchase order value of a bus rolling stock vehicle without obtaining preapproval or requiring the vehicle manufacturer to provide a performance bond (or other form of security). In order to make an advance payment, the&amp;nbsp;recipient must meet certain requirements. For example, the recipient must have a signed purchase order and an executed contract with a vehicle manufacturer that includes advance payment provisions.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
